

#
# Conventional Commit Guide
#   https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#summary
#
#----------------------------------------------------------------------
# STRUCTURE:
# <type>([scope])[!]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPE LEGEND:
#    feat:     New feature for the app or library
#    fix:      Bugfix
#    perf:     Efficiency and latency tuning
#    chore:    Maintenance, tooling, and deps
#    refactor: Cleanup (no behavior change)
#    docs:     Documentation only updates
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# SCOPE LEGEND:
#    infra:  Build machinery, CI, Toolchains (Makefile, Husky, scripts)
#    proto:  The shared contract (stats.proto, generated types)
#    core:   Shared Go internal logic (transport, collectors)
#    ui:     The visualization layer (React, Canvas, UI logic)
#    lab:    Specific research implementations (labs/*)
#    meta:   Project-level docs and identity (README, LICENSE)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# SIMPLE EXAMPLE:
#    chore(meta): update readme
#
# COMPLEX EXAMPLE:
#    feat(proto)!: transition wait_delta to nanoseconds
#
#    Standardize all scheduler telemetry on nanoseconds to avoid 
#    precision loss in high-frequency sampling (100Hz+).
#
#    BREAKING CHANGE: SchedStat.WaitDelta is now uint64 (ns). 
#    Consumers must update their scaling logic from ms to ns.
#
#    FIXES: #42
#    IDEA: We can use a bit-shift for normalization if CPU cost spikes.
#    TODO: Update UI line-chart axis scaling
#    TODO: Fix lab-01-ghosthunter parser to match new type
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
